The paper deals with the problem of computing joins, which is a fundamental problem in database systems and falls under the category of data management (cs.DB). The authors use a geometric framework to design an algorithm that achieves the fractional hypertree-width bound, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the use of multidimensional data structures, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The authors mention the use of logical resolution, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents results that go beyond worst-case scenarios, which could be classified under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
